                                                           Qwen Business Unit of Alibaba, China\n                                                                                     2\n                                                                                         TongYi AI Lab of Alibaba Group, China\n                                                 liuchengwei.lcw@alibaba-inc.com, mullerxue@126.com, yanhaoyin.yhy@alibaba-inc.com\n\n\n\n                                                                      Abstract\n                                          We propose a lightweight multi-path alignment network\n                                          (LMPAN) for on-device joint acoustic echo cancellation (AEC)\narXiv:2607.02062v1 [eess.AS] 2 Jul 2026\n\n\n\n\n                                          and noise suppression (NS) in full-duplex spoken dialogue sys-\n                                          tems. To address hardware-induced distortions and dynamic\n                                          acoustic conditions, we introduce three core innovations: (1)\n                                          a multi-path alignment stage correcting temporal and energy\n                                          mismatches across reference, linear AEC (LAEC) output, and\n                                          microphone signals; (2) an attention-based mechanism that\n                                          dynamically integrates enhanced LAEC and microphone fea-                 Figure 1: Full-Duplex Spoken Dialogue Architecture.\n                                          tures under varying acoustic scenarios; (3) a post-filtering mod-   ditional signal processing components [12], typically incorpo-\n                                          ule with a dynamic target generation strategy for downstream        rating a linear AEC (LAEC) module based on adaptive filter\n                                          tasks (ASR, VAD). Furthermore, we adopt a two-stage train-          algorithms to suppress linear echo components. Additionally,\n                                          ing framework leveraging self-supervised learning representa-       multi-task learning frameworks [8,13,14] have shown effective-\n                                          tions to enhance perceptual quality. Experiments show that LM-      ness in acoustic scenarios by jointly addressing NS, DRB, and\n                                          PAN, with only 480K parameters and 126 MACs, achieves per-          AEC, leading to overall improvements in speech quality. To\n                                          formance comparable to the state-of-the-art lightweight model       address time-varying latency, prior works [8, 15, 16] proposed\n                                          DeepVQE-S, while ensuring real-time inference capability.           attention-based frameworks that integrate dynamic time align-\n                                          Index Terms: Acoustic echo cancellation, noise suppression,         ment with parallel encoder structures to enhance AEC robust-\n                                          multi-path alignment, dynamic target generation, full-duplex        ness. Some studies incorporate data augmentation and post-\n                                          spoken dialogue                                                     processing strategy to reduce the mismatch for downstream\n                                                                                                              tasks such as automatic speech recognition (ASR) and voice ac-\n                                                                1. Introduction                               tivity detection (VAD) [4, 9, 17].\n                                                                                                                   Despite these advances, existing frameworks remain vul-\n                                          Full-dup